edge sharing and collaboration with other SBU commercial teams. Market Fundamentals \u2013 Provide fundamental markets analysis to support SBU commercial activities. This includes evaluating and summarizing third party/vendor provided supply, demand, and market structure analyses; facilitating the development of AES fundamental market views (e.g., price formation; scenarios; weather); and looking around the corner to where value is migrating. Advanced Analytics \u2013 Lead the advancement of commercial advanced analytics including machine learning applications, predictive analytics and potential blockchain applications. The Portfolio Strategy & Analytics Lead will deliver management presentations and interact with other functional areas such as generation operations, business development, risk management, finance, and regulatory, as needed, with respect to the aforementioned accountabilities. Experience and Qualifications:???????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????? 10+ years combined experience in aforementioned areas, for a commercial organization involved in power generation and trading. 2+ years experience in a leadership role, preferably with experience leading change and introducing new ways of working in an organization Strong cross-functional skill sets: valuation & quantitative analysis; commercial mindset; understands markets, instruments, & market rules; understands correlation of risks and opportunities across the value chain; familiarity with market data & sources, analytical tools and systems. Ability to define a vision of success and drive towards it; can organize and promote agile and efficient workflows; global mindset; can work collaboratively across functions and across cultures; appetite to learn and innovate.???????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????? Ability to connect people and resolve confli